text: Caroline Rask (born 25 May 1994) is a Danish football midfielder who currently plays for A.C. Milan in the Serie A. She has previously played for Fortuna Hjørring, in Denmark's top-division Elitedivisionen and has also played for the Danish women's national team. Rask joined Fortuna Hjørring in 2011 and made her senior international debut as a substitute for Pernille Harder in Denmark's 2-2 tie with Portugal during the 2015 Algarve Cup – during which she also scored her first international goal. ==Honours== ===Club=== ;Fortuna Hjørring Champion * Elitedivisionen: 2013–14, 2015–16, 2017-18, 2019-20 * Danish Women's Cup: 2016, 2019 ==References== ==External links== * Danish Football Union (DBU) statistics * Fortuna player profile * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Danish women's footballers Category:Denmark women's international footballers Category:Fortuna Hjørring players Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:People from Vesthimmerland Municipality
